  &lt;Comment&gt;
    &lt;Title&gt;Acute surgery unit&lt;/Title&gt;
    &lt;ScreenName&gt;Anthony Smith&lt;/ScreenName&gt;
    &lt;CommentText&gt;I got hit by a car cycling home from work suffering 7 broken ribs, a broken collarbone and severe soft tissue damage. I was admitted to the ASU as the consultants wee considering surgery. I spent 7 nights there and I cannot thank or praise the staff enough. Staff went above and beyond to make you feel comfortable and always greeted you with a smile. These traits cannot be taught, it is a caring nature and attitude that not enough people have. The ladies that brought round the food were amazing and I will never forget the lady that gave me two cups of coffee every morning for my caffeine fix. Little things mean so much when you are unwell. My only negative comment is about the consultants. They appear in a whirlwind followed by an entourage of ‘mere mortals taking notes and pandering to their every whim. I never once knew who they were, what they were talking about and what they had come to see me for. They need to slow down, explain who they are and particularly why they are coming to see you. It’s a very daunting experience when you are being pumped full of strong pain relief and hooked up to numerous machines bleeping constantly. Anyway, my experience was a positive one and I thank each and every person that has got me back on the road to recovery. It’s been 4 weeks and I am still struggling but getting there none the less. A large box of Hotel Chocolates was my only way of saying thank you and I hope they enjoyed them. &lt;/CommentText&gt;
